
Overview of noun traction

The noun traction has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                     
1. grip, traction, adhesive friction -- (the friction between a body and the surface on which it moves (as between an automobile tire and the road))
2. traction -- ((orthopedics) the act of pulling on a bone or limb (as in a fracture) to relieve pressure or align parts in a special way during healing; "his leg was in traction for several days")
